LA Visibility Policy - understood as some kind of Usage Control, controlling the usage of given asset - **MUST** contain a target Asset (a product-offering/catalogue), the source-marketplace as an Party role 'odrl:assigner', 'urn:user' (the customer on sink-side) as Party function 'odrl:assigner' and at least one of a Permission or Prohibition rule. Such a Visibility Policy is related to source's product-offering/catalogue and will be enforced on sink's side: sink's application will show only those information, authorized by source to end-user (e.g. an acting user on sink-side).|Language: en
